&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Buyer (Apprentice) - 37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting new opportunity for an Apprentice Buyer to join our busy CHoICE Procurement Services Team based at Sunderland Royal Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have already achieved a good standard of education at GCSE (or equivalent) level and possess excellent customer service and organisational skills. Good and clear verbal communication and interpersonal skills are vital to this role as you will be liaising with a wide range of people both within the organisation, and outside the organisation to support our purchasing function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated individual who has the drive, ability and enthusiasm to work within a dynamic, strategically challenging and rewarding environment aligned to the modernisation of purchasing and supply in healthcare. You must have good IT skills, be numerate and have an eye for detail as the ability to work accurately is key in this role to ensure we, as a team, deliver a high quality service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The duration of the apprenticeship will be 24 months subject to regular reviews to demonstrate progress. Apprentices complete L3 Business Administrator Apprenticeship standard and are paid a percentage of the wage until they have successfully completed the apprenticeship. We also offer a supportive learning environment and encourage staff to build skills through work-related courses and internet based learning.&lt;/p&gt;
